%main.work
    %section.summary
        %p.large Tuft & Needle was struggling to compete in the increasingly crowded mattress industry. Competitor copycats made differentiation incredibly hard while competitors’ shady marketing tactics drowned our message.
        %p.large We chose to focus on increasing the usability of our site as the primary way to increase conversion rate. I pulled together a team of UX designers, user researchers, engineering managers, and project managers across three product teams to work on improvements spanning the site funnel.

    %section
        %h2.s4 Identifying problem areas through a usability benchmarking study
        %p To help identify problem areas (and serve as a means of measuring improvements), our user researcher conducted a usability benchmarking study across 15 metrics on nine major site pages. Meanwhile, I used Google Analytics to review page performance and identify the most significant areas of drop-off in our funnel. 
        %p Following our initial research, I facilitated three ideation workshops, one each with the Customer Acquisition, Product Discovery, and Purchase Experience product teams. Using the benchmarking study as our guidepost, we ideated ways to improve usability and increase conversion. 
